reviewText: So much truth and transparency in the show, & that was amplified even more in this segment where the ideas behind the creation are shared.
I love this show, and it is fascinating to hear the conversation between the creator and the stars of this wonderful program.
Parenthood is absolutly an asome team of actors that come through on real family situations every week, and every season
Most favorite show ever! Love the entire cast! I can relate to every story line. I feel as though I personally know the braverman family!

I've been watching this show since it started, the thing that kept my attention was that the family deals with realistic problems.  This panel is great, I like seeing the actors not in their roles and Dax Shepard steals the show and keeps it funny!
Loved it!  What I learned about the show, characters, storylines, and actors helped me become even more vested in the show.
This was fun to watch and learn more about the beloved characters and the writing process of my favorite show.
It was interesting seeing the cast being themselves. However, with such a large cast, the interview seemed a bit slow at times.

It was interesting to see my favorite show's actors out of character. It was great to hear creator's
thoughts and processes for the various episodes.
Only reason for not giving it 5 stars was that it was distracting to try to listen to one
person, but hear others in background giggling, whispering, etc...Maybe would have been better to have
others turn off, but that probably is impractical. Good and worth the watch!

Parenthood has become my most favorite TV show due to it's realistic and believable portrayal of this special TV family. Watching the actors and producer interact speaks volumes as to how and why this show is able to capture the hearts of it's viewers.

Wonderful
And informative show with the main characters.

Loved the show so watching the actors fill us in on the journey was special. The show itself  can really pull on the emotional strings so it was definitely well written. Fave characters were Adam & Kristina and would like them to do a spinoff

I tuned into watching Parenthood in the first place for Lauren Graham after watching her in Gilmore Girls - which turned out to be one of the greatest shows ever made in my opinion.
As a HUGE fan of Parenthood, it was interesting to learn some of the "behind the scenes" stories
This is one of the best series we have followed!
Love this show.  I'm binge watching.  I think I have tears every episode.

I have been watching this show since it first started & the first show had me hooked. The dynamics in each of the families characters of this show were just equisite & defined by each one they are closest to. This show sheds light on the inner workings of a group of outstanding all around people like us...who make this story so unique & funny...Sharing light on different episodes & taking questions from audiences & people who have come from around the world to show their compassion & true appreciation to this show
I love Parenthood's cast and the show! They are so down to earth, just like as portrayed on the show!! Loved it
Love the show
Awesome wrap-up after Season 4. Love the actors' personalities and how they all blend together that shows how much of a family they are even outside the show.
Excellent and hilarious! Awesome way to connect with this amazing Parenthood cast!
Love this show!  Fun to see the cast actually talk about it!
A good watch if you love the Parenthood characters which I do.  Lots of fun insights into the show.
Fun to see.
Fun to watch and experience their real life relationships.

If you are a fan of Parenthood who is waiting for season 6 to show up free on Amazon or Netflix, watch this panel of Parenthood actors sharing their comments about earlier seasons of the show. They exude mutual respect for the show's creator and you'll learn more about each. And now I love Dax shepherd even more, almost as much as I love Lauren Graham.
The Best Ever show I have seen in all my life!
Anything live at Paleyfest is wonderful - if you love TV!
Enjoy seeing the actors of my favorite show as themselves
I love the show. This was fun to watch.
The PaleyFest cast insight on how the show is made and the cast interviews.
Peter Krause didn't say much and lost interest.
Interesting and very enjoyable.
I enjoyed it
Great for fans!
Great show!!
Excellent show!
Well done
Best show on T-V
Cant wait till the series this fall

Such a great video of all the Parenthood actors and how they really feel about the show. Fun seeing how most of them are so similar to the characters they portray and their thoughts on their characters choices.
Love everything Parenthood
Good!
I was so sorry to see the show ended.  This was really the family that many of us wish we had in real life. I am going to miss it.
Love the show

This was so fun to watch! I love the show Parenthood! In my opinion it had the best series finale and show has ever had! So sad when the show ended. This was great though! I think it takes place between seasons 4&5.
Very good. Nice to see the actors as themselves!

I recently watched this show on Amazon Prime Video for free, after watching the entire Parenthood series (all 6 seasons). I truly enjoyed it, as I love this wonderful show! The present cast members have great personalities. I was disappointed, though, that Bonnie Bedelia wasn't present for the show. I recommend this show to anyone who is a Parenthood fan. If you've never watched Parenthood, then get acquainted with most of the main cast members and creator Jason Katims.

I loved this show. I loved the Bravermans. I would love to be in a family like the Bravermans. I'm so sad it's over. I also love Lauren Graham! She is one of my favorite actresses. She is the reason I started the show. I'm really glad I did.
As mentioned in my review of the Season 4, I was delighted to see all the actors on stage, their interaction with one another and the writer of the show.
LOVE Parenthood cast!
